referralInstructions.other:
HOW IS A REFERRAL MADE TO THE SERVICE?

Patients must self-present. There is no electronic booking or call back service.

SERVICE INFORMATION

Pharmacies are often better suited to deal with, signpost or advise on a wide range of health issues. Examples are but not limited to simple sore throats or earache, very minor injuries, colds, coughs . . .

EXCLUSIONS

Emergency Hormonal Contraception (EHC)
Emergency/Urgent Repeat Prescriptions (unless the patient is already known to the pharmacy)
Patients needing these services should be offered another appropriate pharmacy from within DoS (these are clearly named as such).

ADDITIONAL INFORMATION

Pharmacies offer many other services and patients should check before attending if the pharmacy can meet their requirements. These may be Smoking cessation, weight management, health screening etc.

services.name: Pharmacy - Boots the Chemist - Newcastle under Lyme

referralInstructions.other:
HOW IS A REFERRAL MADE TO THE SERVICE?

General problems – In person
Emergency Hormonal Contraception – In person. The woman MUST attend in person no third party supplies are allowed. 

EXCLUSIONS FOR EMERGENCY HORMONAL CONTRACEPTION

No age restrictions. 

INFORMATION TO GIVE TO THE CALLER FOR EMERGENCY HORMONAL CONTRACEPTION

Service can only be provided by an accredited pharmacist so provide caller with details of at least 2 pharmacies to contact to confirm an accredited pharmacist is available.

The woman will have a consultation with the pharmacist, the service is totally confidential but a record will be kept by pharmacy. No patient identifiable data is ever shared.
Supply of Emergency Hormonal Contraception is free of charge.

Additional information

No supply can be made under this service if it is longer than 120 hours since unprotected sex and the woman should be referred to a Sexual Health Service as an intrauterine device is the only remaining option for emergency contraception if it is longer than 120 hours post unprotected sexual intercourse.

Up to 72 hours after unprotected sex the product is Levonorgestrel
From 72 to 120 hours the product is Ulipristal.
